# Orchestration Setup

Intake a complex task, explore the codebase, decompose into slices, and produce an editable `.orchestration/config.yaml` that the user reviews before execution.

**Core principle: plan visibly, execute separately.**

```
User provides source (ticket, plan, description)
        │
        ▼
┌─────────────────────┐
│ orchestration-setup  │
│                      │
│ 1. Validate prereqs  │
│ 2. Parse input       │
│ 3. Explore codebase  │
│ 4. Decompose slices  │
│ 5. Write YAML config │
│ 6. Print summary     │
└─────────┬───────────┘
          ▼
.orchestration/config.yaml  ← User reviews & edits
          │
          ▼
/run-orchestration           ← Separate invocation
```

## Input Sources

The setup skill accepts work from four input types and normalizes into a mandate.

For full input parsing details, see [references/input-sources.md](references/input-sources.md).

| Source | Syntax | Parsing |
|--------|--------|---------|
| **Linear ticket** | `orchestration-setup CAL-123` | Fetch via `linctl` or Linear MCP |
| **Notion page** | `orchestration-setup https://notion.so/...` | Fetch via Notion MCP |
| **Inline description** | `orchestration-setup "Build X with Y"` | Parse directly |
| **Markdown file** | `orchestration-setup ./plans/feature.md` | Read and extract structure |

